               <head>Ludolf of Saxony, <hi rend="italic">Vita Christi</hi>; Germany (Eberbach?), 15th century, first half</head>
               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Laud_Misc_462-item1" n="1">
                     <locus>(fols. 1r-120r)</locus>
                     <author key="person_4949605">Ludolf of Saxony</author>
                     <title key="work_3016">Vita Christi</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                     <rubric>De pascha et diversis huius nominis acceptionibus</rubric>
                     <incipit>Nunc secundum Ieronimum aspergamus de sanguine librum nostrum, ut limina domorum </incipit>
                     <explicit> totius psalterii modulatio cum anxietate cordis et tristitia.</explicit>
                     <finalRubric>Expliciunt meditaciones de vita et moribus Domini nostri Jhesu Christi, qui pauperi eas pie colligenti et cuilibet eis bene utenti dignetur propicius misereri. Amen. Hec Ludolffus Carthusiensis. Item manufidelis et venerabilis patris Ludolffi sic scripsit. Explicit hoc opus collectum ex diversis et pluribus, de quo si quisque quod suum est tolleret parum vel nichil colligenti remaneret.</finalRubric>
                     <note>This is the third volume of a four-volume set; the others are British Library, Arundel 85 and 103, the fourth volume is missing.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fol. 120v)</locus>
                     <title type="desc">List of chapter titles</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                     <rubric>Incipiunt rubrice capitulorum premisse tercie partis Vite Christi</rubric>
                  </msItem>
